pg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1347477692/image_1347477692.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1347477692/image_1347477692.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">jetcityimage</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>Intro &amp; Thesis</h2> <p>I first initiated coverage of <strong>Exxon Mobil Corporation</strong> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/XOM\" title=\"Exxon Mobil Corporation\">XOM</a></span>) stock at the end of <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4565931-exxon-mobil-reality-check-2023\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4565931-exxon-mobil-reality-check-2023\" target=\"_blank\">December 2022</a>. Unfortunately, I had no luck with timing at that time. However, when the stock started to turn around, I wrote my 2nd</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1347477692/image_1347477692.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742030-why-exxon-mobil-is-still-a-buy", "pub_date": "2024-12-04 16:15:06"}, {"id": "4742028", "title": "Above The Noise: Red Wave, Tariff Uncertainty, And Government Spending", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1262884925/image_1262884925.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"American flag for Memorial Day, 4th of July or Labour Day\" data-id=\"1262884925\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"875px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1262884925/image_1262884925.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.